Milan Bakes, a lieutenant in the Czech army set a world record in the kneeling portion of the three position rifle competition en route to a gold medal at the 1990 World Cup USA Olympic-style shooting tournament in Chino, California.
Francoise Decharne of France won the women's air rifle competition in the most closely contested event of the day.
Jasna Sekaric of Yugoslavia won her second gold in the women's air pistol event winning over a South Korean, appropriately named Bang, and a West German.
Sekaric had won gold and bronze medals at the Seoul Olympics. 
